html
    head
        include head.pug
    body
        nav-header
        div
            h1 Git badger
        div
            p
                span Git badger makes your project better through badges. Badge is a simple shild like this 
                badge-shield(badge="eslint-errors", status="10")
                span . Such badges show an actual status of the project. 
                span To make them alive git badger provides an api to store statuses and get actual badge. 
                span Badges provided by 
                a(href="https://shields.io/") shields.io
            h4 Why even do you need badges
                ul
                    li You see actual status of a project.
                    li Badges more informative than plain text or table.
            h4 Use git badger instead of existing services:
                ul
                    li You can't use existing services (you have private repository or incompatible technology stack)
                    li You need specific badges for specific purposes
                    li You need flexible solution
                    li You want to control badge provider (you can deploy git badge by yourself on your machine)
                    li You want to track status history
            h4 Simple steps to make your project better:
                ul
                    li
                        span.icon
                            i.em.em-triangular_ruler 
                        span &nbsp;decide which badges you want to track
                    li 
                        span.icon
                            i.em.em-ambulance
                        span &nbsp;find a way to get current status of project (it must be really simple in 90% of cases)
                    li
                        span.icon
                            i.em.em-rocket
                        span &nbsp;store current status to git badger instance in your CI pipeline
                    li
                        span.icon
                            i.em.em-memo
                        span &nbsp;show badge in project README.md 
                    li
                        span.icon
                            i.em.em---1
                        span &nbsp;you are awesome! Stay that way
            h4 Terminology
                ul
                    li
                        span shield - prepared badge image, provided by shields.io 
                        badge-shield(badge="eslint-errors", status="10")
                    li
                        span subject - left side text of shield. 
                        i eslint-errors
                    li
                        span status - current status of badge subject, at right side of shield. 
                        i 10
                    li
                        span badge - turn your project statuses to shields. 
                        i eslint-errors 
                        span badge that converts 
                        i 10 
                        span to 
                        badge-shield(badge="eslint-errors", status="10")
        api-reference